  "title": "Finance Officer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>·        Review, approve invoices and prepare payment vouchers upon invoice approval and posting<br />·        Generate reports on incomplete and un-invoiced work orders<br />·        Reconcile vendors’ Statements of Account (SOA) and resolve discrepancies in a timely manner<br />·        Handle Accounts Payable confirmations in response to vendors’ audit confirmation requests<br />·        Prepare and maintain monthly prepayment schedules, including amortisation of prepaid expenses<br />·        Attend to verbal and written enquiries from residents and commercial owners/tenants<br />·        Assist the Finance Manager in the preparation of financial and management reports<br />·        Support the preparation of minutes for EFF meetings<br />·        Provide coverage for cashier counter duties and perform end-of-day closing duties when required</p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p><ul><li>Relevant experience in AP unction</li><li>Able to start work immediately will be an added advantage</li><li>Applicant must be able to commit for 6 months in this role</li></ul></p><p><br />\n\n</p>",
